A suicidal man, Juan Manuel Alvarez, caused a catastrophic train collision in Los Angeles by parking his Jeep on the tracks but fled before impact.
The collision resulted in multiple deaths and injuries, with Alvarez facing at least 10 counts of homicide.
Alvarez, despondent over his marriage, had planned to end his life but changed his mind at the last moment.
Despite initial suicide threats and self-harm attempts, Alvarez ultimately fled the scene, leaving behind a trail of devastation and tragedy.
The incident left authorities and witnesses shocked and grieving over the preventable disaster.
